text: Itransition Group Limited
Master Professional Service Agreement
Agreement # 07102025-07
Name of Customer:
SIGHTWATCHER LTD
Effective Date: October 7, 2025
Customer's company registration number:
Address:
71-75 Shelton Street, Covent Garden, London, WC2H 9JQ, United Kingdom
Customer’s VAT number:
(for UK and EU entities)

WHEREAS, Customer wishes to engage Itransition Group Limited, having its registered address at Third floor, 5-8 Dysart Street, London, EC2A 2BX, UK (“Itransition”) as an independent contractor to provide it with certain services as described in the applicable Statement(s) of Work (as defined below);
WHEREAS, Itransition is willing to provide such services on the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement.

NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing premises and the mutual covenants, promises, obligations and agreements contained herein, and other good and valuable consideration, the sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, the parties, intending to be bound, agree as follows:

Definitions. In this Agreement, the following terms have the meanings specified or referred to in this Section 1 and shall be equally applicable to both the singular and plural forms. Any agreement referred to below shall mean such agreement as amended, supplemented and modified from time to time to the extent permitted by the applicable provisions thereof and by this Agreement.
“Confidential Information” shall have the meaning set forth in Section 5(a) below.

“Deliverables” all documents, products, designs, software, reports, plans and other materials or items of any kind developed or provided by Itransition as part of or in connection with the Services, including any deliverables specified in a Statement of Work.

“Work Product” shall any Deliverables other than the Pre-Existing Intellectual Property and Third Party Materials, including (without limitation) any software applications and any documentation specifically designed or created by Itransition as set forth in a Statement of Work.

“Facilities” shall mean any workspace, telephone and facsimile capabilities, computer network connectivity resources to be provided by the Customer as may be expressly set forth in a Statement of Work.
“Itransition’s Subcontractors” shall mean any subcontractors, suppliers or service providers who were selected by Itransition or one of Itransition’s Subcontractors.

“Services” shall mean the Consulting Services (as defined in Section 2(a) below) performed by Itransition for Customer under the terms of this Agreement, pursuant to and as described in a Statement of Work.

“Statement of Work” shall mean a statement of work agreed and signed by both parties, setting out a description of the relevant Services, Charges and any other material terms.  Unless otherwise specified on a Statement of Work, each Statement of Work shall be governed by the terms of this Agreement and shall be incorporated herein for all purposes. In case of any inconsistency between the terms of the Statement of Work and this Agreement the applicable terms of the Statement of Work shall prevail over the terms of this Agreement. Itransition shall use Statements of Work on a per project basis where the Services that Itransition is to perform and the Work Product are specifically identifiable.  Statements of Work shall be in substantially the form attached hereto as Exhibit A.

“Pre-Existing Intellectual Property” means the software application tools, both in executable code and source code form and pre-existing Itransition material which Itransition has already developed or which Itransition independently develops pursuant to this Agreement. Itransition’ pre-existing intellectual property shall remain the property of Itransition;

“Data Protection Laws” shall mean any data protection laws applicable to processing of Personal data contemplated by the Agreement, including as applicable, UK GDPR, Data Protection Act 2018, EU GDPR and any related decisions or guidelines and subsequent legislation of a similar nature.
"Data subject”, “Personal data”, “processing”, “processor”, “controller” shall have the same meaning as set out in Data Protection Laws.

“Group” shall mean the collection of Itransition Companies that function as a single economic entity through a common source of control legally represented by Itransition Holdco Limited. Itransition is a Group Company.
“Group Company” shall mean a company which is a member of the Group.
Services.
Consulting Services. Itransition will provide consulting and development services as specified in a Statement of Work, according to the terms of this Agreement (“Consulting Services”).

Customer Obligations. Customer will provide Itransition with the Facilities set out in the Statement of Work and shall provide reasonable co-operation, information and access to Customer’s systems and premises as may be reasonably necessary in order for Itransition to perform the Services specified in a Statement of Work.

Changes to Services. No changes to Statements of Work, including changes in scope, shall be effective until agreed upon by the parties and documented in a subsequent amended and signed  Statement of Work.  After a request from Customer for any such amendment, Itransition shall draft a proposed amended Statement of Work for such amendment which shall include an estimate of the reasonable additional costs and changes in time limitations resulting from the requested changes. Upon Customer’s acceptance of such estimates in writing, the terms of such amendment shall replace all the relevant sections of the applicable Statement of Work.

Delays. Subject to the remainder of this clause 2(d), in the event of (i) a delay by Customer in performing any obligation hereunder, (ii) a delay due to Customer’s request for changes to the applicable Statement of Work, (iii) a dispute in good faith between the parties as to whether a particular Work Product meets the relevant specifications, (iv) a delay due to any third party’s (excluding Itransition’s Subcontractors) act, failure to act or delay in performing any obligation whatsoever, or (v) any other delay incurred as a result of Customer’s actions, the delivery of the remaining Work Product shall be deemed postponed for an equivalent period and any time schedule set forth in the applicable Statement of Work shall be deemed amended accordingly. ITranstion shall use all reasonable efforts to mitigate the delay and the impact of any delay, where applicable.  Except for delays incurred under clause (iii) above, no such delay shall relieve or suspend Customer’s obligation to pay Itransition under Section 3 below and, in addition to such payment obligations, Customer shall pay for all reasonable expenses incurred by Itransition in connection with any such delay.
Nonexclusive Services.  Itransition’s services under this Agreement shall be nonexclusive.
Acceptance.  Itransition will inform the Customer in writing on completion of each Deliverable, whereupon:

The Customer will review the Deliverable to determine if it conforms in all material respects to the requirements of this Agreement, including any specifications or acceptance criteria set out in the Statement of Work, and provide Itransition with written approval of the Deliverable or a written statement of defects to be corrected.
The Customer will not unreasonably withhold or delay its acceptance of a Deliverable. If the Customer approves the Deliverable with minor errors, Itransition will fix those minor errors promptly.

If the Customer provides a written statement of errors, Itransition will correct the errors in the Deliverable at no additional cost to the Customer. Itransition will do so within five days after receiving the Customer's statement of errors (Deadline), and inform the Customer in writing when the corrections are complete.

The approval process in this clause 2(g) will then be repeated. If Itransition fails to correct the errors by the Deadline, the Customer may (without prejudice to any other rights or remedies it may have): require Itransition to repeat the process to correct errors; approve the Deliverable subject to a reasonable deduction from the fees to reflect the errors; and/or finally refuse to approve the Deliverable and refuse any subsequent performance which Itransition attempts to make.

If the Customer finally refuses to approve a Deliverable under this clause 2(g), it may (without prejudice to any other rights or remedies it may have) refuse to pay for the Deliverable and require Itransition to refund immediately any sums previously paid to Itransition.
Fees.

Consulting Services. All Consulting Services and their fees shall be expressly set out in a signed Statement of Work and Itransition shall not bill for any fees not expressly agreed in such a Statement of Work.  In consideration for Itransition’s performance of the Consulting Services, Customer shall pay to Itransition the fee(s) set forth in the applicable Statement of Work in accordance with any payment schedule or achievement of any milestones as may be included in the Statement of Work, which may include Acceptance of the relevant Deliverables. Where expressly and specifically indicated in a Statement of Work, Consulting Services shall be provided on a time and materials basis and billed at the hourly rates shown therein.  Amounts and time schedules set forth in the applicable Statement of Work represent an estimate of the hours required to complete the work outlined therein. Itransition will make reasonable commercial efforts to complete the work within the estimated time frames.  In the event that actual hours incurred to complete the work exceed those included in the applicable Statement of Work, Itransition will communicate this to Customer, and either (i) bill the additional hours or days at the same rates as specified in the applicable Statement of Work, or (ii) the parties will negotiate an additional or amended Statement of Work for such additional hours or days. Any additional Consulting Services that Customer requests and Itransition agrees to provide shall be provided on terms to be mutually agreed upon by the parties in a signed Statement of Work.  No payment shall be due for any Services which are not provided or any Deliverables which do not meet the agreed Specification in all material respects, unless expressly agreed in writing.

Expenses.  Customer shall reimburse Itransition for any out-of-pocket expenses reasonably incurred by Itransition in connection with the performance of each Statement of Work which have been specifically agreed in writing in advance, up to the agreed amount.

Invoicing and Payment. Unless otherwise specified in the applicable Statement of Work, Itransition will bill Customer monthly for Consulting Services rendered by sending electronic invoices, with a detailed listing of all work performed and a summary of approved expenses incurred during the preceding month.  Payments are due within thirty (30) days upon receipt of invoice.  Customer will make all payments without right of set-off or charge back.  All payments made pursuant to this Agreement shall be made in GBP.
ITRANSITION DOES NOT ACCEPT PAYMENTS WITH cashier's CHECKS IN A CURRENCY OTHER THAN GBP.

Taxes. Fees do not include any present or future sales ​or value added taxes applicable to the Services or associated expenses. Itransition will separately itemize any such ​applicable taxes on each invoice, or in lieu thereof, Customer shall furnish Itransition a properly executed tax exemption certificate, if applicable. Customer shall be responsible for paying any applicable sales and value ​added type taxes later assessed by a government agency.
Interest & Charges. If Customer does not pay invoices when due, interest will be charged on the unpaid amounts at 0.3% per month on a daily basis.

Services Suspension. Itransition will have the right to suspend the Services and/or delay the Services result until the overdue payment is received. All overdue payments, plus penalty fees, will be required to restart the Services following the suspension.
Proprietary Rights.

Ownership of Deliverables and Work Product. Subject to clause 4(b), Itransition acknowledges that all Deliverables and Work Product created under this Agreement shall be the sole and exclusive property of the Customer. Itransition hereby assigns to the Customer, with full title guarantee and free from all third-party rights, all present and future Intellectual Property Rights in the Deliverables and Work Product. The assignment takes effect immediately upon creation of each Deliverable or item of Work Product. Itransition will, at the Customer’s request and expense, sign any documents or take any other steps reasonably required to give effect to this assignment.

Pre-Existing Intellectual Property.  Itransition’s Pre-Existing Intellectual Property (being any software tools, modules, templates, code libraries or other materials developed or owned by Itransition before the Effective Date or developed independently of this Agreement) shall remain the property of Itransition. To the extent that any Pre-Existing Intellectual Property is incorporated into, or necessary for the use of, the Deliverables or Work Product, Itransition grants to the Customer an irrevocable, perpetual, worldwide, royalty free licence (including the right to use, copy, modify, create derivative works, and sub license) to the extent required for the Customer to use, maintain, and further develop the Deliverables and Work Product.
Third Party Materials.  Except as expressly authorized in a Statement of Work, or otherwise agreed in writing in advance:
Itransition shall not include any third party software or materials in the Deliverables or Work Product; and

Itransition shall ensure that the Customer obtains a perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, and royalty free licence (including the right to use, copy, modify, create derivative works, and sub license) to the extent required for the Customer to use, maintain, and further develop the Deliverables and Work Product.

Delivery and Assistance.  Upon completion or termination of this Agreement, Itransition shall promptly deliver to the Customer all source code, object code, documentation, configuration files, access details, login details, information and other materials necessary for the Customer to use and maintain the Deliverables and Work Product independently. Itransition shall provide reasonable assistance during any transition period to ensure business continuity.

Itransition Restrictions.  Itransition shall not reuse, resell, or otherwise make available any Deliverables or Work Product (or material derived from them) for the benefit of any third party without the Customer’s prior written consent.

Moral Rights Waiver.  Itransition shall ensure that all individuals involved in creating the Deliverables or Work Product waive any moral rights they may have, to the extent permitted by law, so that the Customer may freely use and modify the Deliverables and Work Product.

Indemnity.  Itransition shall indemnify and hold harmless the Customer from and against any and all losses, damages, costs, or expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising out of any claim that the Deliverables, Work Product, or the Customer’s use of them infringes any third party’s Intellectual Property Rights.

Cooperation. The parties hereby agree to cooperate with the other party in: (i) vesting in such party the ownership of the proprietary rights of such party created hereunder; and (ii) assisting such party in obtaining patent, copyright, or any other intellectual property rights in the proprietary rights of such party created hereunder and in maintaining and protecting such proprietary rights, including, without limitation, executing any documents which such party reasonably deems necessary for such purpose. Provided that, Customer shall be responsible for payment of all of Itransition’s reasonable fees and expenses associated with such cooperation.
Confidentiality.

Defined. “Confidential Information” shall have the meaning set forth in the mutual NDA, executed on October 7, 2025 by and between the parties hereto (the “Mutual NDA”) including any such information exchanged prior to the Effective Date.  The parties further agree to comply with all provisions for Confidentiality set forth in the Mutual NDA in respect of such Confidential Information.

Preserving Confidentiality. Each party hereby agrees that it shall comply with each of its obligations with respect to such Confidential Information as are contained in the Mutual NDA referenced above for the duration of this Agreement and all Statements of Work and for an additional  period of 5 years.
Personal Data Protection (General)

Compliance with Data Protection Laws. The parties to this Agreement will comply with Data Protection Laws and the data protection clauses set out in this Agreement and any Statement of Work in relation to any Personal data shared under this Agreement or any Statement of Work.

Obligations of Customer. Customer acknowledges and agrees that it will not provide Personal data to Itransition unless the performance of this Agreement or the relevant Statement of Work requires or involves the use and disclosure (“use”) of such Personal data. Customer confirms (i) that it has competence and necessary authorisation from all relevant data subjects, as required under Data Protection Laws, in order for Itransition to use such Personal data in accordance with this Agreement, and (ii) that such data subjects have been given necessary information regarding its use.
Personal Data Protection (Itransition as controller).

Itransition as controller. Itransition will act as a controller in relation to  certain Personal data received from Customer, such as names, surnames, e-mails, phone numbers, positions of Customer’s employees and its other representatives or suppliers, for any of the following purposes: (i) providing the Services, (ii) maintaining and using relevant IT systems, (iii) quality and risk management activities, (iv) providing Customer with information, including by means of electronic communication, about Itransition and other Group Companies and its and/or their range of services, (v) disputes and litigation, (vi) confirmation of provision of the Services for Customer, and (vii) complying with any legal requirements or requirements of a professional body of which Itransition or its employees are members.

Forms of processing. When acting as a controller, Itransition will process Personal data on paper as well as in electronic form, for as long as necessary to provide the Services under this Agreement, safeguard its rights and/or fulfil its obligations resulting from applicable laws, regulations or professional standards.

Data transfers to subcontractors. When acting as a controller, Itransition may transfer Personal data shared with it to other Group Companies, subcontractors, legal advisors and/or insurers in relation to any of the purposes set out in this clause 5 (d). Some of these recipients may be located outside the United Kingdom and/or European Economic Area. Itransition will carry out such transfers only where it has a lawful basis to do so, including (i) to a recipient who is in a country which provides an adequate level of protection for Personal data; or (ii) under an instrument which covers the Data Protection Laws for the transfer of Personal data outside the United Kingdom and/or European Economic Area.
Personal Data Protection (Itransition as processor).

Personal data processing agreement. Where the Services under this Agreement or any Statement of Work involve Itransition processing any Personal data on behalf of, or under the instructions of, Customer, the relevant Statement of Work shall include any clauses required by the Data Protection Laws in agreements between controllers and processors.   In case the transfer of such Personal data to a third country, which does not ensure an adequate level of protection within the meaning of Data Protection Laws, is required, an instrument which covers the Data Protection Laws  requirements for the transfer of Personal data to data processors outside the United Kingdom and/or European Economic Area shall be executed before any transfer.

Non Solicitation. During the Term and for a period of one (1) year thereafter, each party agrees not to hire, solicit, nor attempt to solicit the services or business of (i) any employee of the other party and/or any employee of the other party’s affiliates or (ii) any former employee who was employed by the other party and/or its affiliates within two (1) year of such solicitation, in each case, without the prior written consent of such other party. In the event one party wishes to hire the other party’s employee and/or any employee of the other party’s affiliates, first party shall obtain a written approval from other party and pay an obligatory pecuniary compensation in an amount of not less than 30,000 (thirty thousand) GBP for each employee or the amount of the annual salary of such employee, whichever is greater.
Indemnity, Warranty and Liability.

Indemnity. Itransition will, at its expense, defend and indemnify the Customer against a claim that Itransition, in performing the Services to be rendered under this Agreement or any Statement of Work, infringed a patent or copyright and will pay all losses, liabilities, damages, claims and related expenses (including attorney fees and disbursements) either awarded by court or agreed to in an out of court settlement, subject to the limitations set forth below in this Section 7(a) and 8. Notwithstanding the above, Itransition shall have no liability under this Section 7(a) for any claim of infringement based on (i) modifications, adaptations or changes to any Work Product not made by Itransition, (ii) the combination or use of any Work Product with any materials not furnished or selected by Itransition, if such infringement would have been avoided by use of the Work Product alone, (iii) the use or incorporation of any materials supplied to Itransition by Customer, or (iv) any infringement necessary in order for Itransition to comply with Customer’s specifications.  In the event any Work Product is held to, or Itransition believes is likely to be held to, infringe the intellectual property rights referenced above, Itransition shall have at its option and expense the right to (a) modify the Work Product to be non-infringing;  (b) obtain for Customer a license to continue using the Work Product; (c) substitute the Work Product with other work product reasonably suitable to Customer or (d) if none of the foregoing remedies are commercially feasible, terminate this Agreement, refund all fees actually paid by Customer other than fees which relate to Deliverables which have been Accepted.  THE INDEMNITY AND OTHER REMEDIES SET OUT ABOVE STATE CUSTOMER’S SOLE AND EXCLUSIVE REMEDIES AND ITRANSITION’S SOLE AND EXCLUSIVE OBLIGATIONS WITH RESPECT TO THE INFRINGEMENT OF INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS.

Customer shall defend, indemnify and hold Itransition and all its affiliates and their respective officers and directors harmless from any third party claims and any reasonable related costs and expenses that arise in connection with use of any materials provided by Customer including (without limitation) intellectual property infringement claims caused by such materials.

Indemnification Procedures. If either Party (the Indemnitee) becomes aware of a claim which may require indemnification, they will promptly notify the other Party (the Indemnifying Party) in writing of the claim and subject to this Section 7(c) will allow the Indemnifying Party to assume full control of the defence and settlement of the claim.  Subject to this Section 7(b), the Indemnitee will provide the Indemnifying Party with all assistance and information necessary to defend and settle the claim.  The Indemnifying Party shall have no obligation to indemnify the Indemnity if the Indemnity fails to promptly notify the Indemnifying Party in accordance with this Section 7(c).

Warranty. Each party represents and warrants to the other party that it has the full power, right and authority to enter into and perform this Agreement with the other party.  Itransition further represents and warrants that the Services will be performed in a professional manner, consistent with generally accepted industry standards. Itransition warrants that all Deliverables shall perform in accordance with the specifications and descriptions in the relevant Statement of Work in all material respects for a period of 12 months from Acceptance.  Subject to the foregoing warranties, Itransition does not warrant that the Services, the Work Product provided hereunder will be entirely free from non-material errors or defects.  Customer warrants that it owns or has the right to provide to Itransition Customer’s Confidential Information.  Itransition warrants that all Work Product provided under this Agreement shall be in compliance with all intellectual property laws and any other nation or sovereignty, and international treaties and agreements; Customer’s sole remedies for breach of this warranty are provided in Section 7(a) and 7(c).  EXCEPT AS SET FORTH IN THIS SUBSECTION 7(D), ITRANSITION MAKES NO WARRANTY, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED IN CONNECTION WITH THE SERVICES, THE WORK PRODUCT, INCLUDING THE RESULTS AND PERFORMANCE THEREOF, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION ANY IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, NONINFRINGEMENT OR FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.
Liability.

References to liability in this section 8 include every kind of liability arising under or in connection with the Agreement including but not limited to liability in contract, tort (including negligence), misrepresentation, restitution or otherwise.
Nothing in the Agreement shall limits any liability for:
death or personal injury caused by negligence;
fraud or fraudulent misrepresentation; and
breach of the terms implied by section 2 of the Supply of Goods and Services Act 1982 (title and quiet possession); and
any other liability which cannot legally be limited.

Subject to clause 8(b) each party’s total liability for breach of any indemnity, breach of clause 4(a) (assignment of IP), breach of clause 5 (confidentiality and data protection) shall not exceed £1,000,000.

Subject to clauses 8(b) and 8(c), each party’s total liability for all other loss or damage shall not exceed the total Charges paid to Itransition under the relevant Statement(s) of Work in the 12 month period leading up to the breach giving rise to the liability.
Term, Termination and Suspension.

Term.  The initial term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall end on the one year anniversary of the Effective Date unless earlier terminated in accordance with this Agreement (the “Initial Term”).  On each anniversary of the Effective Date, this Agreement shall automatically renew for an additional one (1) year period unless either party gives the other party written notice of its election not to renew the Agreement at least sixty (60) days prior to the next anniversary of the Effective Date.  The start date, duration and renewal terms of any Statement of Work shall be set out in the relevant Statement of Work.

Termination for Breach. Either party may terminate this Agreement or any outstanding Statement of Work if the other party is in material breach of the terms of this Agreement or such Statement of Work and has not remedied the breach within fifteen (15) days of written notice specifying such breach.
Immediate Termination. In addition to the foregoing, this Agreement may be terminated immediately on written notice to the other party as follows:
(i) either party may terminate if the other party becomes insolvent or unable to pay debts as they come due, or ceases to so pay or makes an assignment for the benefit of creditors; or
(ii) either party may terminate if the other party is dissolved or liquidated.

Termination With Notice. In addition to the foregoing, either party may terminate this Agreement or any outstanding Statement of Work by providing the other party 60 days’ advance written notice of such decision to terminate.
Effect of Termination. Upon termination of this Agreement or any applicable Statement of Work for any reason:
Services for such Statement of Work shall cease at that time;

Itransition shall deliver to the Customer all information and materials provided to Itransition by the Customer, (Service Information) or created as part of the Services under such Statement of Work, including all documents, papers, notes, working papers, manuscripts and typescripts, computer disks and tapes, materials, equipment, technical information and data, files, reports and any other property or Confidential Information belonging to the Customer;
Itransition shall delete and shall procure that its staff, any Itransition Subcontractors and their staff delete any Service Information on any IT equipment;

Itransition shall, if so requested by the Customer, provide all assistance reasonably required by the Customer to facilitate the smooth transition of the Services to the Customer or any replacement supplier appointed by it;

Customer shall pay all amounts due and payable under this Agreement for all Deliverables which have been Accepted and all Services properly rendered by Itransition up to the date of termination. Notwithstanding the foregoing the Customer may, at its sole option, reclaim and recover any advance payments made to Itransition in relation to a Statement of Work, or any which were paid for Deliverables which have subsequently been rejected or cancelled or Services which have not, in the reasonable judgement of the Customer, been satisfactorily performed as of the date of termination.

all rights and obligations provided under Sections 3 (to the extent any fees or taxes remain unpaid or expenses have not been reimbursed), 4, 5, 6, 7, 8 and 10 shall survive such termination for any reason; provided, however, that Section 5(b) and Section 6 shall survive for a period of three (3) years following such termination for any reason and Section 7 shall survive such termination for a period of one (1) year following such termination for any reason; and
termination will not affect any claim, demand, liability or right of Customer or Itransition which accrued prior to such termination.

Itransition will have the right to delay the provision of assets created during the course of the Services to Customer until all Services related to creation of the aforementioned assets are paid in full by Customer.
Miscellaneous.

Injunctive Relief. The parties acknowledge that any breach or threatened breach of the provisions of Section 4, Section 5 or Section 6 may cause irreparable harm and significant injury to an extent that may be extremely difficult to ascertain.  Accordingly, the parties agree that either party may, without waiving any remedy under this agreement, seek from any court having jurisdiction any interim or provisional relief.

Assignment. Neither Party may assign this Agreement, or any rights or obligations hereunder, in whole or in part, without prior written consent of the other Party. However, no consent is required for assignment by the Party to a related business entity while retaining substantially the same ownership, or in the case of change of control through merger, acquisition, re-capitalization, or a similar transaction, ​provided that the party provides the other party with reasonable advance notification ​.

Relationship between the Parties and third party rights​. Neither Customer nor Itransition is a legal representative, agent, or a partner of the other.  Specifically, Itransition is an independent contractor for all purposes herein, and any personnel retained or assigned to perform the Services hereunder shall at all times be considered employees, agents, or contractors of Itransition, and at no time employees of Customer.  Each party will be solely responsible for payment of all compensation owed to its employees, as well as employment related taxes.  Each party will maintain appropriate worker’s compensation for its employees as well as general liability insurance.   The transactions contemplated hereby are not intended to, and shall not be interpreted to constitute, a joint venture, partnership or similar relationship between the parties hereto, and neither party hereto shall be deemed to be liable or responsible for the liabilities or obligations for the other party hereto except as specifically provided in the indemnification provisions set forth in Section 7. This Agreement does not give rise to any rights under the Contracts (Rights of Third Parties) Act 1999 (or any equivalent legislation in any jurisdiction) to enforce any term of this Agreement. ​

Mutual Responsibilities. At the time of executing this agreement, both Itransition and Customer shall name key personnel who will be responsible for acting as a primary source of contact for interactions on the project. The parties shall work together to progress the Project in accordance with terms herein using reasonable care and skill in their work and dealings with each other and third parties who may become involved in the Project.

Marketing and Publicity. Customer grants Itransition a non-exclusive, non-transferable, royalty-free, worldwide license to use Customer’s name, logo, and trademark solely for the purpose of identifying Customer as a client in Itransition’s websites and marketing materials. This permission is revocable by Customer at any time with written notice.

Force Majeure. Except for obligations to pay money for Services received, neither party shall be liable for any failure or delay in performance of its obligations hereunder on account of strikes, riots, fires, explosions, acts of God, war, governmental action, or any other cause which is beyond that party’s reasonable control.

Entirety. This Agreement, the Mutual NDA and all applicable Statements of Work incorporated herein constitute the complete agreement between the parties and supersedes all previous and contemporaneous agreements, proposals, or representations, written or oral, concerning the subject matter of this Agreement.  This Agreement may not be modified or amended except in writing signed by the Director of Itransition and a duly authorized representative of Customer.  Subject to this Section 10(g) and Section 2(c) above, no other act, document, usage, or custom shall be deemed to amend or modify this Agreement or any Statement of Work, as applicable.  It is expressly agreed that any terms and conditions of any prior communications between Itransition and Customer shall be superseded by the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the applicable Statement of Work.
Severability. In the event any provision of this Agreement is held to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Agreement will remain in full force.
Governing Law/Venue. The English laws will govern this Agreement ​and, subject to (j) below, the parties submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the English courts ​.

Dispute Resolution. Except for action seeking a temporary restraining order or injunction, or suit to compel compliance with this dispute resolution process, the parties agree to use the dispute resolution procedures set forth in this Section 10(j) with respect to any controversy or claim arising out of or relating to this Agreement or its breach.

Informal Dispute Resolution.  For a period of 30 (thirty) days after notice from either party, the parties shall attempt in good faith to resolve the dispute by direct negotiation of non-lawyer representatives of the parties.

Mediation.  If the parties do not resolve the dispute within such 30-day period, either Party may submit the matter to mediation with a professional mediation service selected by the parties.  Good faith mediation is a condition precedent to arbitration or litigation.  If the parties do not resolve the dispute through mediation or if 90 (ninety) days have passed since the parties submitted the dispute to mediation and the parties are not in active negotiations, either Party may submit the dispute to the next step in the dispute resolution process.

Arbitration.  Any dispute ​arising out of or in connection with this Agreement, including any question regarding its existence, validity or termination, shall be referred to and finally resolved by arbitration under the London Court of International Arbitration Rules (“Rules”), which Rules are deemed to be incorporated by reference into this Section. The number of arbitrators shall be one. The seat, or legal place, of arbitration shall be London, England. The language to be used in the arbitral proceedings shall be English. Nothing in this Section 10(c) will prevent or delay either party from: (a) seeking orders for specific performance, interim or final injunctive relief in the English courts; (b) exercising any rights it has to terminate the Agreement; or (c) commencing any proceedings in English courts where this is necessary to avoid any loss of a claim due to the rules on limitation of actions. The arbitrator will have no authority to award any damages that are excluded by the terms of this Agreement.

In the event of arbitration, filing fees and costs shall be paid initially by the complaining party. The arbitrator shall award to the prevailing party reasonable costs and fees, including attorney fees.

Limitation periods. The parties agree that any action in relation to an alleged breach of this Agreement shall be commenced within two years of the date of the breach being discovered. Any action not brought within that two-year time period shall be barred, without regard to any other limitations period set forth by law or statute.

Waiver. The failure by either party to enforce at any time any of the provisions of this Agreement, or to exercise any election or option provided herein, shall in no way be construed as a waiver of such provisions or options, nor in any way to affect the validity of this Agreement or any part thereof, or the right of either party thereafter to enforce each and every such provision.

Notice. All notices  required or permitted under this Agreement shall be in writing and shall be sent by registered or certified mail, postage prepaid or transmitted by telegram or telefax if confirmed by such mailing, to Customer and Itransition at their respective addresses set forth on page 1 of this Agreement.  Either party may change its address by written notice to the other.
Subcontracting. Customer hereby approves and consents that Itransition may subcontract Services or part of the Services under this Agreement for their remote performance to its affiliated companies.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties hereto, by their duly authorized representatives, have set forth their signatures as of the date first set forth above.
